revision.text:
'''Kagoshima Gosha''' (鹿児島五社) refers to five shrines located in the Kanmachi district of {{ill|Kagoshima Prefecture|ja|鹿児島県}} {{ill|Kagoshima City|ja|鹿児島市}}, said to have been enshrined by the {{ill|Shimazu clan|ja|島津氏}}. They are also known as '''Kanmachi Gosha''' (上町五社) due to their location in the Kanmachi area.<ref>[http://www.city.kagoshima.lg.jp/_1010/kanko/database/category/shiseki/area_central/kanmachi/_34763.html 上町五社] - 鹿児島市 Accessed December 28, 2011.</ref> These shrines are strategically concentrated in the northeastern {{ill|Kimon|ja|鬼門}} direction from the center of Kagoshima City.

Historically, many were extensively supported by the {{ill|Satsuma Domain|ja|薩摩藩}}, often on a grand scale. However, in modern times, with increased car usage and easy access to major suburban shrines, as well as competition from newer shrines such as {{ill|Terukuni Shrine|ja|照国神社}}, some shrines lost their buildings entirely. Later, the shrines underwent renewed interest; notably, Nanpo Shrine rebuilt its shrine building in 2010.<ref>[http://www.47news.jp/localnews/kagoshima/2010/12/post_20101230112631.html 社殿再建、元日に五社参り復活 鹿児島市の南方神社] - 47NEWS Accessed October 1, 2012.</ref>

<gallery>
File:Nanpo Shrine in Kagoshima.JPG|First: {{ill|Nanpo Shrine (Kagoshima City)|ja|南方神社 (鹿児島市)|lt=Suwa Shrine|lt_ja=諏訪神社}}
File:Yasaka shrine in Kagoshima.JPG|Second: {{ill|Yasaka Shrine (Kagoshima City)|ja|八坂神社 (鹿児島市)}}
File:Inari shrine in Kagoshima.JPG|Third: {{ill|Inari Shrine (Kagoshima City)|ja|稲荷神社 (鹿児島市)|lt=Kagoshima Inari Shrine|lt_ja=鹿児島稲荷神社}}
File:Kasuga Jinja in Kagoshima.JPG|Fourth: {{ill|Kasuga Shrine (Kagoshima City)|ja|春日神社 (鹿児島市)}}
File:Kagoshima Wakamiya Shrine.JPG|Fifth: {{ill|Wakamiya Shrine (Kagoshima City)|ja|若宮神社 (鹿児島市)}}
</gallery>

