{{translated page|ja|鹿児島五社|version=92643094|comment=Imported full ja history}}

'''Kagoshima Gosha''' (鹿児島五社) refers to five shrines located in the Kanmachi district of {{ill|Kagoshima Prefecture|ja|鹿児島県|12=draft}} {{ill|Kagoshima City|ja|鹿児島市|12=draft}}, said to have been enshrined by the {{ill|Shimazu clan|ja|島津氏|12=draft}}. They are also known as '''Kanmachi Gosha''' (上町五社) due to their location in the Kanmachi area.<ref>[http://www.city.kagoshima.lg.jp/_1010/kanko/database/category/shiseki/area_central/kanmachi/_34763.html 上町五社] - 鹿児島市 Accessed December 28, 2011.</ref> These shrines are strategically concentrated in the northeastern {{ill|Kimon|ja|鬼門|12=draft}} direction from the center of Kagoshima City.

Historically, many were extensively supported by the {{ill|Satsuma Domain|ja|薩摩藩|12=draft}}, often on a grand scale. However, in modern times, with increased car usage and easy access to major suburban shrines, as well as competition from newer shrines such as {{ill|Terukuni Shrine|ja|照国神社|12=draft}}, some shrines lost their buildings entirely. Later, the shrines underwent renewed interest; notably, Nanpo Shrine rebuilt its shrine building in 2010.<ref>[http://www.47news.jp/localnews/kagoshima/2010/12/post_20101230112631.html 社殿再建、元日に五社参り復活 鹿児島市の南方神社] - 47NEWS Accessed October 1, 2012.</ref>

